article.headline: Louisiana-Lafayette 72, Fla. International 62
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Travis Bureau scored 18 points to lead Louisiana-Lafayette to a 72-62 win over Florida International on Wednesday night. Maurice Barksdale had 11 points for Louisiana-Lafayette (10-12, 6-5 Sun Belt Conference) and Elijah Millsap added 10 points and nine rebounds. La'Ryan Gary finished with eight points for Louisiana-Lafayette. Russell Hicks led the Golden Panthers (6-16, 3-9) with 15 points. Chris Fuller and Alex Galindo finished with 12 points each for FIU, which has lost seven of its last eight. Galindo also pulled down eight rebounds, and Tremayne Russell added 10 points. After a tight first half, Louisiana-Lafayette entered the break with a 35-26 lead, and never gave it up. The Ragin' Cajuns led by as many as 18 points in the second half. Florida International closed the gap to 68-62 with 1:08 left to play, but Louisiana-Lafayette made a layup and two free throws to seal the win.
